<br>
I would like to offer a counter proposal to the BB rules (which I think no one is overly happy about):<br>
<br>
Because the minimum number required to post a raid basically make the big brother rules a moot point, lets track the individual epic items instead.<br>
<br>
For example: the following is the warrior epic quest components:<br>
<br>
1) unjeweled dragon head hilt - lake rathe<br>
2) Diamond<br>
3) Black Sapphire<br>
4) Jacinth<br>
5) Damaged Dragon Head Hilt<br>
6) Ball of Everliving Golem (fear golems)<br>
7) Giant Monocle<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  A keg of vox tail ale<br>
9) A Block Of Perma frost<br>
10) frozen goblin heart<br>
11) 2 Rebreathers <br>
12) Ancient Blade (Queen of Chardok)<br>
13) Tiny Lute. <br>
14) Green Dragon Scale (Severlious)<br>
15) Red Dragon Scale (Nagafen, Talendor)<br>
16) Maestro's Hand (Maestro)<br>
17) Spiroc Wingblade (Spiroc Lord)<br>
<br>
From this list, there are only 2 rare drops needed from the planes, the golem ball (which can be done at any step, including last) and maestro's hand (which has to be done before the the Spiroc lord)<br>
<br>
Therefore, my proposal is this - we make a list (forum) for each class that is moderated.  That list will be a first in first out que with whoever has the other components on top of the list.<br>
<br>
With this scenario, ANY warrior with red and green dragon scales and the ancient blade can sign up for maestro's hand.  Once the spiroc lord is dead they can sign up for the ball of golem (ok - that won't happen because of how common it is).<br>
<br>
I believe (with the proper spin) would be accepted by most guilds.  It does have an inherent benefit to the current epic guilds because they are the only ones that can acquire the dragon scales.  It does not exclude the small guilds either.<br>
<br>
The rule I propose would be to replace the BB rules:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> To use this calendar, guilds must agree to honor the epic item list.  The lists track who is furthest along in their epic weapons quest and have all other possible components.  Guilds agree to contact the next on the list and give allow them to loot the epic item because the same curtsy will be returned.<br>
<br>
An epic item list will exists for each class that requires components from the plane of hate and plane of fear.  Players can sign up for the next epic item drop when they have all other components.<br>
<br>
The intent of this is to not &quot;take&quot; items from guilds killing the gods in the planes.  The intent is to maximise the number of epic items entering The Rathe.  Every player on the Rathe has EQUAL shot at an epic item with this system because ANYONE with the other components will be placed on the list.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p><TABLE background="http://rampages.onramp.net/~jrey/backg.gif"><TR><TD><IMG src="http://rampages.onramp.net/~jrey/elawndarhead.jpg" border=0></TD><TD><P><font color="white">      "You will never become a Knight at this rate"<BR><BR><BR>"Me 'barsh.  Just heal Pally"</font></P></TD><TD><IMG src="http://rampages.onramp.net/~jrey/elaundarhead.jpg" border=0></TD></TR><TR><TD><P align=center><font color="white">Elawndar<BR>Warrior 51</font></P></TD><TD><P align=center><font color="white">Frayed Knot<BR>The Rathe</font></P></TD><TD><P align=center><font color="white">Elaundar Nobillium<BR>Paladin 53</font></P></TD></TR></TABLE></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubiasschmias.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bias Schmias</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Toede Slavedriver</span><br>  Posts: 146<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(1/25/01 1:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: New way to do the Epic Calendar:</span><hr size=1> Elaundar, i have a lot of respect for you, but that is one of the worst ideas i've ever seen. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
There is already enough problem communicating with people about which guild is the big brother and how THAT works.  setting up lists for loot is just a horrific logistical nightmare.<br>
<br>
And it also guarantees a widening gap between the 'haves' and the 'have nots' on the server.  Just imagine the howling from people who go on a raid with their guild, kill the Maestro, the hand drops, and a_random_warrior is brought up, loots &amp; leaves.<br>
<br>
I don't like the rules rewena posted (about needing permission from other big brother guilds to join friends on a raid), but if it is acceptable to the people who will be impacted by it (ie, the BB Guilds) i'll accept it.<br>
<br>
Really, as far as I'm concerned, the Big Brother details of how it works should be up to the calendar admins and the big brother guilds.  It doesn't affect me at all.  But to completely change the epic loot rules so that people who do the work &amp; manage to luck out and get the loot don't even have a shot at looting it is going to simply foment hatred for people perceived as 'uber'.<br>
<br>
And I wouldn't support that system.  I'd quit going to the planes before I'd go up with my guild, clear to maestro, kill him, and then let someone loot the hand while we rez our dead and get ready to move on.<br>
<br>
But this thread should be about what the big brother guilds want to do, and how they want to handle big brothering and epic looting &amp; guesting on raids if you're in a BB guild.<br>
<br>
my brief take:<br>
<br>
guesting - fine by me.  you have friends, use 'em. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
bb - 1 week rotation per plane (fear/hate), noted on calendar.  ideally have someone chat up the raid leader as the raid starts and give them contacts/backup contact info.<br>
<br>
Penalty:  If a god is left up / bb not called in, the raiding guild loses posting rights for two months.<br>
<br>
2am exception rule:  If the BB guild is called in, they will immediately contact and work with the next-day raid to notify them that the god will be coming down, but there may be some over-run on the time.<br>
<br>
It is more important that the god go down quickly than someone has their 2am cutoff time respected.  This can be REALLY problematic on the weekends, i realize.  Tradeoff:  If any non-epic god loot drops and the god is killed after 2am PST, the god loot goes to the next-day raid.  This is to encourage guilds to call in big brother early.  Additionally, if the next day guild has enough people, ALL loot that drops after 2am goes to them.<br>
<br>
Or ...<br>
<br>
BB assistance has a cutoff time of 3am PST, but only for purposes of killing the god.  After 3am, everyone packs up and goes home, and tries again tomorrow.  Any incident like this will be reviewed by the admins/BB representatives to determine if it was just poor luck or if sanctions are in order.  For a late-night call-in attempt that is too late to bring the god down, i suggest a maximum sanction of losing the next raid in that plane only.<br>
<br>
Additionally, if a Big Brother guild is listed as being 'on call' for a week, and fails to have the manpower available to take a god down in a timely fashion (ie, you only have 10 people on, everyone's in bed or on a trip or whatever), then that guild loses their next months' BB rotation slot.  If someone calls you in and you can't do it, that's just as bad as not calling you in.<br>
<br>
But anyway, whatever the epic guilds decide to do for managing/handling epic rotation, I'll respect it.  It's really y'alls job to figure it out and handle it.  The rest of us are just here to come screaming when we can't kill cazic. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Bias Schmias<br>
51st Warrior<br>
