<br>
1 - If your guild is on a raid and things go badly, that's a shame, but 'a lack of preparation on your part does not constitute an emergency on mine.'  There should be a penalty for going past the 2am time and leaving the god up.  If you're not willing to risk it, call in the epic guild early &amp; often.<br>
<br>
2 - it acts as a way to ease the minds of the next-day raiders who might see a god raid going past 2am as infringing on their time.  If they get all post-2am loot, it may make it easier.<br>
<br>
But I honestly agree with Morty.  I don't know how really 'necessary' the epic guild rotation is.  especially with the new posting rules which make almost every posting entity capable of taking a god down.<br>
<br>
But I do know that from a political/diplomatic standpoint it is necessary because without it certain powerful guilds would attempt to filibuster the calendar system again, and nobody wants that.<br>
<br>
Bias Schmias<br>
