This is what i was gettin at:<br>
<br>
How sure are we that BotB could have killed ct in the alloted time?<br>
<br>
LoM was extremely confident they could kill ct in teh time given, and a few mistakes occurred, causeing serverwide outlash on them for not calling bb. Bots had made a trade with LoM, to loot the shisshar head. But, in leiu of my feelings on the 6 friends loophole, 6 friends did not enter.<br>
And they didnt finish up on ct in time, and angered a bunch of folks.<br>
<br>
Do i believe 6 lvl 60 bots could have made the raid successful? possibly, probably, but no way to know for sure. Judging from how close they were, i'd lean toward yes.<br>
<br>
Do i believe that taking out the 6 high level keg members from the BotB raid could have had the exact same results at Lom? Possible, probable, but no way to know for sure. Again, i ask had BotB ever killed ct completely on their own? If they have, soley by themselves, consistently then it weakens my argument; however if they never have, or have one time by the skin of their teeth, then it strenghthens my agrument - in effect keg bb'd botb, and took mfh's place that night.<br>
<br>
Again, in principle, the callender is made to share planar loot amongst the multiple entities on an overcroweded server. Again, the bb epic rotation was created a) to ensure gods were downed promptly, b) the rotation was set up to ensure some even form of distribution amongst the epic guilds.<br>
<br>
If a non bb guild can kill a god completely unassisted, then for all i care they can give the ct skin to jobabar if they want, or to a friend, or bank it, or whatever. But if they cant, then they are abliged, by rules, to ask for help. The burden of proof is on them. Not on speculation. Not on a bb guild claiming how easy ct is, how he can be snared, yawned, feared, etc.. <br>
<br>
Did keg/botb break a rule? No. <br>
Should keg/botb be punished? No.<br>
Do the rules need to be ratified? ABSOLUTELY.<br>
<br>
My input on bb/friend rules:<br>
<br>
If a non bb guild has fear/hate on god day, and they wish to give out epic items to members in bb guilds, the bb members should wait outside zone. Imo, this proves, beyond a doubt, that bb was not needed, therefore removes all suspicions of using loopholes.<br>
<br>
It should be illegal for 6 bb members to enter a plane when a god is up, using the 6 friend ruling, because many believe, including myself, that 6 high level vetrans can actually make or break a raid.<br>
<br>
This clause should apply to trades as well. If a bb guild/member negotiates a trade with a non bb guild, the recipient of that epic item should, again, wait outside the zone until the item is obtained. This will prevent suspicions/skeptecism, and will still allow for generous gestures to friends, while also allowing for the bb rotation to take place.<br>
<br>
Furthermore, if a gift/trade is made, AND no bb members assist in any way, i do not feel that the looting of the item(s) would represent a 'slot' in the bb rotation - because it was, infact, an unassisted gift/trade.<br>
<br>
Gimme your thoughts on this. I took 2 days to try to think of a reasonable solution/suggestion. I'm curious to see how the community responds. <br>
